./CHANGELOG.md:438:- Added depth-2 pedals-to-key end-to-end test coverage (frac-0101): `tests/test_pedals_to_key.py` now includes `PedalsToKeyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/pedals_to_key.py` public surface through expressive pedal phrases: sustain and expression combine into chord-hold, tension, extension, volume, and brightness guidance; rapid on-off-on gestures resolve to `modulate`; held landings resolve to `pedal_point`; phrase batches, playback plans, renderer controls, and primitive diagnostics round-trip through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_pedals_to_key_depth.py` pins the pedals-to-key test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4610 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:632:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
./CHANGELOG.md:771:- Folded the highest live octave down by one octave at playback time: `voice_shaping.py` now marks the extreme top band with a `pitch_multiplier`, and `play_voice()` applies that fold before sending OSC so CypherClaw's brightest instruments stop landing in the most painful register.
./CHANGELOG.md:776:- Made face captions harmonic-function-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `cadence_type` for `Resolution` and `Afterglow`, so the same hook can resolve differently under dominant, plagal, authentic, and deceptive harmonic landings.
